<body>
  <%- include('../partials/navbar') %>

    <main id="main-content" class="container page-main accessibility-page">
      <header class="page-header">
        <h1>Accessibility &amp; Social Impact</h1>

        <p class="lead">
          This page documents the accessibility learning and social innovation experiences that shaped my interest in inclusive digital systems and accessibility-aware software testing.
        </p>
      </header>

      <section class="text-section">
        <h2>Accessibility learning</h2>

        <p>
          My accessibility learning developed through a mix of formal training, independent study, and practical project
          work. This included accessibility-focused learning through APX, Deque, and university-based activities that
          helped me understand accessibility as more than a compliance checklist.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="text-section">
        <h2>Social innovation</h2>

        <p>
          Accessibility also connected with my interest in social innovation and inclusive digital participation.
          Through work such as the Wisdom social innovation endeavour and the CQU Changemaker credential, I began to see
          digital accessibility as both a technical responsibility and a social impact concern.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="text-section">
        <h2>From idea to capstone</h2>

        <p>
          This interest later shaped the direction of the Online Accessibility Governance Platform. I proposed and
          helped carry the accessibility-focused project idea through planning, requirements, documentation, team
          coordination, and final capstone delivery.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="text-section">
        <h2>Current focus</h2>

        <p>
          My current accessibility focus is on practical evidence: understanding barriers, documenting issues clearly,
          connecting findings to standards such as WCAG, and thinking about how accessibility problems can be remediated
          in real software projects.
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>

    <%- include('../partials/footer') %>

